Base damage = 1_power_level_damage * power_level * armor_multiplier
Base damage = 600_hero_power * armor_multiplier

Calculating power level for a specific hero power value
Armor category per enemy type and other breed info

Resulting damage = base_damage +
 base_damage*(crit_and_or_headshot_multiplier - 1) + 
base_damage*(backstab_multiplier - 1) + 
base_damage*(damage_boost_multiplier - 1)
Drinking a strength potion applies damage boost and turns damage against Armored, Berserkers and Super Armor to Infantry damage
Backstab multiplier is 1.5 only on Shade's ability, otherwise it is just 1
Resulting damage against players is multiplied by 0.1 for Champion, 0.25 for Legend and 0 for all other difficulty levels. But melee weapons don't do FF damage.
Resulting damage is rounded to the nearest quarter

Hero power buffs are applied to base damage;
Crit power buffs are are not applied to the base damage or the crit multiplier, they basically create new multipliers using what's called a boost curve

Cleave value determines how many enemies can be hit by an attack.
For each enemy its hit mass value is subtracted from cleave value until it's <= 0
Against Bosses, Armored Bosses and Lords, additional multipliers are applied to each part of damage separately.
